Key Match Events: Ja Morant recorded a 12th career triple-double with 26 points, 10 rebounds, and 14 assists.
Milwaukee Bucks fell to their fourth straight loss after opening with a win over Philadelphia.
Post-Match Reflections: Ja Morant expressed pride in his team's effort after the comeback win.
Milwaukee coach Doc Rivers acknowledged the need to find ways to get stops when making shots.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Brook Lopez was Milwaukee's next-highest scorer with 12 points.
Seven Grizzlies players, including all five starters, scored in double figures.
